---
import ServicePageLayout from '../layouts/ServicePageLayout.astro';

const faqSchemaObject = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Should I repair or replace my HVAC system?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "If repairs cost more than 50% of a new system or your unit is over 15 years old, replacement is usually more cost-effective."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How long does a full HVAC installation take?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Complete system installation typically takes 1-2 days depending on the complexity of your home's setup."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What SEER rating should I choose?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "For Orange County's climate, a 14-16 SEER system offers the best balance of efficiency and cost. Higher SEER ratings save more energy for a higher upfront cost."
      }
    }
  ]
};
---

<ServicePageLayout
  title="HVAC Installation in Stanton, CA | Hilo Heating and Air"
  description="Professional new HVAC system installation for homes and businesses in Stanton, CA and surrounding Orange County areas. Proper sizing and expert setup from HiLo Heating & Air."
  heroTitle="New HVAC System Installation in Stanton, CA"
  heroSubtitle="If your heating and cooling system has been struggling, a patch job probably won't cut it for long. Hilo Heating and Air handles new HVAC system installation throughout Stanton and Orange County."
  faqSchema={faqSchemaObject}
>
  <section class="pt-4 sm:pt-8 pb-16 sm:pb-24 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 prose prose-lg">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-brand-blue mt-0 mb-4">What Goes Into a New HVAC Installation</h2>

      <p>If your heating and cooling system has been struggling lately, a patch job probably won't cut it for long. At Hilo Heating and Air, we handle <strong>new HVAC system installation</strong> for homes and businesses throughout Stanton, CA and the wider Orange County area. Maybe your old unit finally gave out, or you're working on new construction — either way, our technicians get the job done right the first time.</p>

      <h2>Why Homeowners Choose Hilo Heating and Air</h2>
      <p>Installing a <strong>new HVAC system</strong> isn't cheap, so picking the right contractor matters. We've built our name on fair pricing, solid workmanship, and showing up when we say we will. Before recommending anything, our team looks at your home's layout, insulation, existing ductwork, and how you actually use your space day to day. We're not in the business of pushing whatever unit happens to be sitting in the warehouse.</p>
      <p>We carry equipment from major manufacturers, so whether you need a central air conditioner, a furnace, a heat pump, or a ductless mini-split, our <strong>HVAC installation</strong> team can walk you through what fits your home and your budget.</p>

      <h2>How the Installation Works</h2>
      <p>Every <strong>new HVAC system installation</strong> starts with us actually walking through your property — checking ductwork condition, electrical capacity, and airflow before we recommend a system size. This step gets skipped too often by other companies, and it's usually why people end up with units that are too big, too small, or just plain inefficient.</p>
      <p>Once we land on the right equipment, our crew takes care of everything: removing the old system, adjusting ductwork where needed, wiring it up properly, and running a full test before we pack up. We'll also show you how your new thermostat works so you're not left guessing.</p>

      <h2>What You Actually Get From a Professional Install</h2>
      <p>A properly done <strong>HVAC installation</strong> protects more than just your comfort — it protects your warranty too. Manufacturers can void coverage if a system wasn't installed to spec, which happens more than people realize with unlicensed or rushed jobs. Our technicians follow code and manufacturer guidelines on every install.</p>
      <p>Beyond that, you're looking at lower energy bills, quieter operation, and noticeably better air quality inside your home. And with Hilo Heating and Air, there's no surprise pricing after the fact — what we quote is what you pay.</p>

      <h2>Ready to Get Started?</h2>
      <p>Don't wait for your system to fail completely before calling someone. Reach out to Hilo Heating and Air for a free consultation on your <strong>new HVAC system installation</strong>, and see why so many homeowners around Stanton, CA keep coming back to us.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</ServicePageLayout>
